<section class='masthead masthead-large masthead-cs' id='masthead'>
	
	<%= image_tag 'geo-bg.jpg', :class => "bg", :alt => "GeoSLAM Background" %>
	<div class="wrapper">
		<h1><span class="hp-title-one case-study-header__small">Case study</span><span class="hp-title-two"><br />GeoSLAM</span></h1>
	</div><!--end wrapper-->
</section>

<section class="main-screen">
	<div class="wrapper">
		<div class="overlay header-video">
			<%= image_tag 'geo-home-lg.png', :class => 'main-vid-item', :alt => "GeoSLAM home page" %>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>


<section class="case-study__section--white case-study--background">
	<div class="wrapper">
		<h2>Background</h2>
		<div class="row cf">
			<div class="col3"></div>
			<div class="col7">
				<p>GeoSLAM are a Nottingham based technology start-up who develop survey solutions for the measurement and mapping of multi-level three-dimensional environments. Working alongside the team at GeoSLAM we produced a striking design that incorporated some of the fantastic 3D point cloud imagery form their scanning products. The new bespoke built WordPress site not only looks fantastic but is also easy to navigate, update and is optimised for mobile and desktop devices.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="col2"></div>
		</div><!--end row-->
	</div>
</section>

<section class="case-study__section--grey case-study--design_images">
	<div class="wrapper wrapper-wide">
		<h2>Design</h2>
		

		<div class="case-study-imgset cf">
			<div class="img-l-sm">
				<%= image_tag 'geo-iphone@2x.jpg', :alt => "GeoSLAM website on Iphone" %>
				<%= image_tag 'geo-icon@2x.jpg', :alt => "GeoSLAM website iconography" %>
			</div>
			<div class="img-r-lg">
				<%= image_tag 'geo-dt-under@2x.jpg', :alt => "GeoSLAM website iconography" %>
				<div class="img-hover">
					<%= image_tag 'geo-dt-over@2x.png', :alt => "GeoSLAM website iconography" %>
				</div>
			</div>
			
		</div>

		<div class="row cf">

			<div class="col3"></div>
			<div class="col7">
				<p>At its heart Buildcloud is about information &amp; communication so the design needed to put this to the fore. The interface was kept clean, clear and simple with a minimal core colour pallet. Subtle animations where used to provide greater context when interacting with the user interface.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="col2"></div>
		</div>

	</div>
</section>

<section class="case-study__section--white case-study--wp">
	<div class="wrapper">
		<h2>Technology</h2>
		<div class="wp-container cf">
			<div class="wp-logo">
				<%= image_tag 'wp-w-logo.svg', :alt => "WordPress logo" %>
			</div>
			<div class="wp-info">
				<p>GeoSLAM wanted to be able to make minor text edits to the site as well as add content such as new staff members, image &amp; video galleries, case studies and news stories. WordPress was the ideal platform to use to provide this functionality. We producted a bespoke built theme to maximise the speed of the site and customised the back end interface to make updates to the site a doddle. </p>
			</div>
			
		</div>
		
	</div>
</section>

